            "bestRating": "5",
            "worstRating": "1"
          },
          "reviewBody": "I still remember those days when we were looking for a good school for Myra’s admission.  We had seen a couple of schools however something always seemed to be missing. But the day we visited  Gurukul for the first time, Myra smiled broadly and she said mummy, papa I will study in this school and we couldn’t disagree with her because there was something different about this school from the moment we entered it.\n\nOver the years Gurukul has proved our decision right. We have seen our shy child turn into a confident and happy girl.  I would like to thank each and every member of this amazing institution who has contributed to her growth.\n\nA very special thanks to the School Head - Sushmita Ahlawat ma’am, Director of Academics - Prabha Verma ma’am, all the teachers, non-teaching staff, and the front desk office staff of Gurukul. You have made Myra what she is today.\n\nI wish you all the Best! Please keep inspiring and changing the lives of the students who will come to Gurukul in the future. God Bless you all!\nRaymond shah\nParent of Myra Raymond class 5\nGurukul The School Crossings Republik",
